article.description: ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. -- Amy Beggin scored 19 points and Eileen Weissmann added a career-high 17 to help New Mexico upset TCU (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) 60-53 on Saturday.
article.headline: Beggin's 19 points help New Mexico upset TCU
article.linkText: TCU knocked off by Beggin-led New Mexico
article.story:
ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. -- Amy Beggin scored 19 points and Eileen Weissmann added a career-high 17 to help New Mexico upset TCU (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) 60-53 on Saturday.

Helena Sverrisdotter scored 14 to lead the Horned Frogs (15-5, 5-2 Mountain West), who shot just 17 of 57 (29.8 percent) from the field. It was a ragged game from the outset, with both teams struggling to find a shooting touch.

After leading 21-19 at halftime, New Mexico (13-7, 5-3) found its rhythm in the second half. Midway through the period, New Mexico trailed 37-35, but the Lobos reeled off seven straight points that put them ahead to stay.

TCU climbed back to within 44-42 before Beggin hit consecutive 3-pointers to push the lead to 50-42 -- the largest advantage of the game.
